commit.message:
Add CI checks

* Docker image with toxcore and relevant dependencies
* Github actions to build linux and run tests
* Github actions to build windows

Fix build on non-unix systems

clang supports gcc everywhere, gcc supports asan on linux, mingw doesn't
support it. This is likely an overly restrictive condition, but we only
need the asan to run on one set of tests. This is good enough to have
the asan run most of the time but not break the windows build.

Fix build on older cmake versions

target_link_options was only introduced in 3.13. We need to support 2.18
so swap command for an equivalent target_link_libraries

Remove undefined/implementaion defined behavior on realloc

realloc has implementation/undefined behavior when using realloc with
size 0. Force a manual free in all cases where this is possible

Fix memory corruption in deferred lists

This fixes two bugs.

1. memcpy has undefined behavior when copying into overlapping memory
   regions.
2. We accidentally were copying num_deferred_packet bytes instead of
   num_deferred_packet elements

Switch to memmove which has defined behavior for overlapping memory
regions and fix the copy size.

The address sanitizer has been enabled for unit tests. This forces
failures on bad memory access but breaks the use of `ctest -T memcheck`.
For now I think it is more valuable for our tests to force failure on
invalid memory.

Bump cmake_minimum_required to 2.8.12

* CMake is warning about < 2.8.12 going EOL

Add option to install mocks (default off)

* Resolves #4

Initial review updates

* Naming updates/clarifications
* Fix leaks
* Fix null accesses
* Fix off by one errors
* Fix typos

Merge pull request #2 from anthonybilinski/add-license

Add GPLv3 license file
